# Environment Configuration for Binary Executable

## Example .env file for Bee Server binary

# Server Configuration
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=production

# OAuth Configuration
OAUTH_SERVER_URL=https://your-oauth-server.com
OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret

# Database Configuration (if using MySQL)
# DB_HOST=localhost
# DB_PORT=3306
# DB_USER=bee_user
# DB_PASSWORD=your_password
# DB_NAME=bee_database

# Session Configuration
# SESSION_SECRET=your-secret-key-here

# API Keys (add as needed)
# API_KEY=your-api-key

## Instructions

1. Copy this file to the same directory as your binary executable
2. Rename it to `.env`
3. Update the values with your actual configuration
4. Run the binary - it will automatically load these settings

## Notes

- Lines starting with # are comments
- Remove # to enable a configuration option
- Keep secrets secure - don't commit .env files to version control
